# Pin all text to LF across Windows edits + WSL/mini (Order NW-1).
# A Windows editor flipped ai_capex_cycle.yaml AND cli.py LF->CRLF mid-order,
# producing whole-file line-ending churn that masked real changes. text=auto
# lets git detect text vs binary; eol=lf normalizes every detected text file
# to LF in the repo regardless of how the working file was written, so diffs
# show only real content changes. Binaries are auto-detected and left alone.
* text=auto eol=lf
# Explicit (redundant under the wildcard, kept for intent clarity).
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.yml text eol=lf
